From: stopless-java-gc <noreply@anthropic.com>
Subject: [PATCH 0025/N] macroAssembler_aarch64: add mov(Register, uintptr_t) for CHERI

Companion to patch 0010. The single CHERI-only
`mov(Register, intptr_t)` overload added there resolves call sites
that pass `intptr_t` (signed __intcap). But call sites passing
`uintptr_t` (unsigned __intcap) values — e.g. `mov(rscratch1,
markWord::biased_lock_mask_in_place | markWord::age_mask_in_place |
markWord::epoch_mask_in_place)` at macroAssembler_aarch64.cpp:546 —
still tie ambiguously between `intptr_t` (needs signed conversion)
and the existing `unsigned long long` (needs cap-to-integral
conversion). Same fix pattern as patch 0015 for Address.

Add an explicit `mov(Register, uintptr_t)` overload under
`__CHERI_PURE_CAPABILITY__` so a uintptr_t argument matches
exactly.

Refs: docs/05_zgc_cheri_collision_report.md §6 (patch 0025)

--- a/src/hotspot/cpu/aarch64/macroAssembler_aarch64.hpp
+++ b/src/hotspot/cpu/aarch64/macroAssembler_aarch64.hpp
@@ -516,6 +516,7 @@
   // overload so call sites like mov(dst, src.as_constant()) where
   // as_constant() returns intptr_t do not suffer ambiguous-overload errors.
   inline void mov(Register dst, intptr_t imm64)            { mov_immediate64(dst, (uint64_t)(uintptr_t)imm64); }
+  inline void mov(Register dst, uintptr_t imm64)           { mov_immediate64(dst, (uint64_t)imm64); }
 #endif

   inline void movw(Register dst, uint32_t imm32)
